title.narrative: Project Supporting the Efficient Management of State Resources - GERE

description.narrative: (Haiti): With FY 2020 funds, the Project Supporting the Efficient Management of State Resources (GERE) will contribute to the decentralization efforts of the Government of Haiti (GOH) by addressing long standing issues that impede better governance. The project will advance the Mission's objective to improve independent and accountable GOH institutions. With an all-Haitian staff and a consortium of two local institutions--the Institute for Training and Services (IFOS) and the Center for Training and Technical Coaching (CFET), RTI International is well-placed for this governance initiative. The Project will assist select municipal, departmental, and central level GOH entities' ability to integrate best governance practices to better plan, deliver, and monitor public services and to combat corruption. GERE will leverage past, current, and upcoming development efforts to facilitate demand-driven, locally owned, and effective coordination and collaboration in development programming, including the findings of the Organization for Economic Development and Coordination's public governance review. GERE will also assist key GOH institutions to build leadership and advocacy skills at the national and local levels and support them to better understand their roles and responsibilities and strengthen their governance processes and mechanisms while increasing civic engagement. By using analytical tools such as Gender Equity and Social Inclusion and political economic analysis, GERE will ensure the integration of women, youth, and marginalized populations. Given the volatility of the Haitian governance landscape, the project will use an adaptive management approach to reach its objectives and integrate methods to resolve community disputes. The project will also strengthen champions in parliament and link with others at national and local levels. GERE will develop a donor database and an action plan to improve coordination and collaboration. ......
